cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about transfer learning-based medical image classification, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach to mitigate the insufficient labeled data problem, which involves learning the projection function from source to bridge and from bridge to target, indicating that it may fall under the category of ML (cs.LG - Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging acquisition modality, which suggests that it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves the use of a bridge database, which is a common technique in AI (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with classification, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR - Information Retrieval).
